Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.45,0:00:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Na shining comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.16,0:00:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.62,0:00:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the first two-hour special!\NTry your hand at the two cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.54,0:00:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.12,0:01:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Great Detective is Cornered!\NTwo Big Murder Cases in a Row"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.92,0:01:56.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Agasa Residence
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Hear me out, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.55,0:01:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. I'm listening, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku left early this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.85,0:02:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and came home totally drunk again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.85,0:02:07.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo Yukiko, Shinichi's mother and actress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.64,0:02:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he makes me so mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.60,0:02:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't help it.\NDad's a popular novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has to socialize\Nwith all kinds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.11,0:02:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose lipstick is on his shirt, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.95,0:02:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so mad! I'm gonna cheat on him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:21.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo Yusaku, World-renowned mystery writer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.95,0:02:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.83,0:02:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? I assume\N that was Yukiko-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.42,0:02:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was complaining\Nabout her marital strife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.42,0:02:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad coming home drunk,\Ndad cheating on her...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.59,0:02:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Cheating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.55,0:02:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.68,0:02:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All he thinks about is mysteries.\NHe'd never be that good-for-nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.60,0:02:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, their fights are almost\Nannual events. No point in worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They're so close they argue a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:02:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, how are things with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, with Ran-{\i1}kun{\i0}.\NAre you getting along well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She gets mad every time I call her.\N"When will you finally be back?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we almost see too\Nmuch of each other every single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.51,0:03:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not take a break from your\Ncases and go somewhere with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Autumn is the season for love!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The season for love indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:34.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.32,0:03:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your own business!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that tone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.49,0:03:45.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kisaki Eri, Ran's mother and attorney
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.24,0:03:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I am, trying to give you another client.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if I need your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.08,0:03:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't blame me when business\Nisn't going well, Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:04:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thank you for worrying\Nabout me, Great Attorney!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These two are having\Ntheir own marital spat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Autumn's the season of love? Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Autumn's the season of hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry home, Ran. I'm starving...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for Conan?\NHe's asleep on the sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.95,0:04:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Dozing off in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.00,0:04:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes! I'll make something right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.88,0:04:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! At least take\Nyour glasses off when you sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.63,0:04:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This face... I've seen\Nit somewhere, long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.81,0:04:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.11,0:05:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? G-Give back my glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you're\Nalways wearing glasses, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.32,0:05:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when sleeping\Nor taking a bath. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Isn't that obvious?\NI have bad eyesight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.12,0:05:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-And I can't relax\Nwithout them always on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.05,0:05:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.59,0:05:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might this be the\NMori Detective Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.97,0:05:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you're the one\Nshe shamelessly sent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.02,0:05:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.85,0:05:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's "she"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.73,0:05:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom, Kisaki Eri-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NRight, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.61,0:05:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? No way!\NMom asked for your help?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're both getting along!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means you're pretty\Nmuch back together, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You set this up, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.33,0:06:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it seemed\Nstrange that she'd call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.63,0:06:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids shouldn't be\Nmeddling with adults' affairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so wrong with doing this?!\NI want Mom to come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've made things even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what brings you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:22.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo Nanae (42)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.93,0:06:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually about my husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who died one week ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.69,0:06:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Died? You don't think\Nhe was killed, do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.15,0:06:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I think it was suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.65,0:06:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.99,0:06:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On that day, one week ago,\NI left him alone at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't find him when I returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I worriedly checked his\Nspecial room in the basement...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.22,0:06:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...where I found his cold\Nbody lying on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had swallowed poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.97,0:06:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:07:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A policeman called it\N"aconitine," or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aconitine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.32,0:07:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A type of poison that causes denervation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's found in the leaves\Nand roots of wolfsbane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.99,0:07:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just two milligrams is lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a powerful toxin that causes\Ndeath minutes after ingestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But where would\Nyou come across that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mountains are full of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.71,0:07:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wolfsbane is used in Chinese medicines,\Nminus the poison, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I mean you, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Television! A monster in Masked\NYaiba mentioned it the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.22,0:07:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "I'll kill you with this aconitine,\Nextracted from wolfsbane!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been a thoughtful\Nmonster to explain the poison like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, were you the only\None who found the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.41,0:08:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I was with my\Nhusband's three pupils.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pupils?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.33,0:08:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, my husband\Nand I are both magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.71,0:08:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband, Tsukumo Motoyasu,\Nwas maybe even world-renowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.72,0:08:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo Motoyasu?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know him! He was on the news!\NThey said a great magician had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.10,0:08:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you ever watch\Nis horseracing, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.35,0:08:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? We all went to\Nhis magic show a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.02,0:08:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, I think there's\Na photo of us with Tsukumo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.77,0:08:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was at that show that I\Nmet your wife, Kisaki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.32,0:08:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. So that's why you're here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Kisaki-{\i1}san {\i0}has been\Nour attorney ever since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.75,0:08:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.38,0:08:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find the photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.22,0:09:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I guess I was mistaken!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! You should ask\Nabout those three pupils!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.61,0:09:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.15,0:09:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, is Sanada Kazumi-{\i1}kun{\i0},\Nour magic troupe's ace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say he's to take over for my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.12,0:09:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, is Miyoshi Mako-{\i1}san{\i0}.\NShe's strong-minded, but greatly skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.54,0:09:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no better female\Nmagician in Japan than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lastly, is Momochi Yuji-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.55,0:09:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't been a pupil for very\Nlong and isn't as skilled as the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.13,0:09:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he shows great promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all wonderful youngsters,\Nand all three live with us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and practice magic every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.14,0:09:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where were they that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were with me at\Na Beika Hotel dinner show,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.48,0:09:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,doing magic for the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was\Nsupposed to come too,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.24,0:09:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he said he\Ndidn't do cheap work...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, those three were at home\Nbefore leaving for the show, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't they have had\Nthe chance to poison him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.71,0:10:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband died while the\Nshow was happening, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.88,0:10:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, couldn't they have secretly\Ngiven him the poison in a capsule?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, my husband would've called\Nfor help after noticing the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a phone in the basement,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the door unlocks\Neasily from the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.64,0:10:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about sleeping pills?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing like that was\Nfound in his autopsy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no strangle marks,\Neverything in the house was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there were absolutely\Nno signs of entry or exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means it\Ncould only be a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.54,0:10:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I just can't imagine my\Nhusband committing suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.41,0:10:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By which you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow is our daughter,\NAyano's, birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:11:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even got her present a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't wait to give it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that sound suicidal to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.68,0:11:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the only unusual thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.14,0:11:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found this on\Nhis desk in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ace of Spades\Nand a Jack are stuck together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police pulled them apart,\Nbut there was nothing written inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put them back\Ntogether to show to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it\Nisn't just a magic prop?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.00,0:11:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my husband never\Nreally did card tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I've never seen\Na prop like this before!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.13,0:11:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Let's just go to her house for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.30,0:11:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always saying, "Let's go!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.56,0:11:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one going.\NYou butt out, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.35,0:11:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on! Take Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He might be helpful!\NHe knows all sorts of unusual things!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.78,0:12:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.78,0:12:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.24,0:12:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! But you better behave yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.54,0:12:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.29,0:12:23.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,With Shinichi at a magic show...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.97,0:12:29.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an impressive mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! The late Motoyasu-{\i1}san\N{\i0}was a world-renowned magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, where is the basement\Nroom where your husband died?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.57,0:12:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Momochi-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.33,0:12:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.83,0:12:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.12,0:12:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You appear to be greatly troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:59.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Momochi Yuji (25) Magician
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no use hiding it. I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you have\Na pigeon in your hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.01,0:13:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's your turn!\NAre you a new student?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.14,0:13:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.73,0:13:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is Mori\NKogoro-{\i1}san{\i0}, a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.90,0:13:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! The famous detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You can't tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's obviously here to investigate
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:30.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyoshi Mako (20) Magician
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Motoyasu-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.62,0:13:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.37,0:13:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.21,0:13:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Little boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and buxom girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.29,0:13:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Buxom?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,White...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.47,0:13:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should at least\Nuse that many pigeons!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.14,0:13:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.48,0:14:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, what is a detective doing here?\NWasn't his death a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.77,0:14:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because he\Nwasn't the type to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, there are those\Nstrange cards. Or so I'd surmise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, these.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These strange cards were on the\Ndesk in the basement where he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the Ace of Spades and\Nthe Jack that were stuck together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.04,0:14:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, isn't this just a prop?\NPlus, the police said it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes. There's nothing to find now,\Neven if you scoured the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is the fact there is now
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.89,0:14:42.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanada Kazumi (27) Magician
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.77,0:14:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only one genius here instead of two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you! You ripped up\Nimportant evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. The real one\Nis in your jacket pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. Aren't you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's him! The genius magician\Nwho dressed up as the Kaito Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.91,0:15:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on that ship during the 60th\Nanniversary party of the Suzuki {\i1}zaibatsu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.30,0:15:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanada Kazumi, at your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.46,0:15:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be wise to leave soon,\Nunless you want to tarnish your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.47,0:15:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems pretty indifferent to\Nthe fact his magic instructor just died...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.64,0:15:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? He used cards\Nwith different patterns just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.65,0:15:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never normally\Ndo this. He's a perfectionist...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.53,0:15:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Sanada-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Ntaken this pretty hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He looked up to my\Nhusband almost as a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the three pupils, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you in Class A?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:45.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo Motoyasu's daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here? Are you here to visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we have some business here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.71,0:15:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of business?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. So this is her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:16:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who has business\Nhere. He just came along, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.60,0:16:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, in that case, want\Nto go shopping with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.10,0:16:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy and I are just\Nabout to go buy an outfit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for my birthday party tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.40,0:16:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got my invitation too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.49,0:16:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Let's go, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s busy right now!\NMaybe some other time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.77,0:16:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.\NKids should play with kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.50,0:16:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano. I'm sorry, but I can't\Ngo shopping today, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.05,0:16:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you promised,\NMommy! You're a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.80,0:16:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy is, too! My birthday\Nis tomorrow, but he's still overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all a bunch of liars! I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, will you go with me?\NI'll coordinate your outfit for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.49,0:16:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.82,0:16:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to bother you, Mako-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, everyone! Back to your cage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.83,0:17:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven't told her\Nher father is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I told her he's\Ndoing a show overseas...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.30,0:17:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This isn't my pigeon.\NIt's Mako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange for her\Nto mistake her pigeons...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her teacher's death\Nmust be hard on her, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.98,0:17:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And magicians are supposed to\Nbe good at concealing themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who\Ndoesn't seem any different!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just recently became a pupil, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.78,0:17:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going to\Nget dinner ready now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.99,0:17:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.12,0:17:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he always make the meals?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our custom is that the newest\Npupil always makes the meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.04,0:17:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.50,0:17:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let us see the basement\Nroom where your husband died.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.23,0:18:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what exactly is\Nthis basement room?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.94,0:18:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was my husband's special room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.32,0:18:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would always hole up in\Nhere and research new magic tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His pupils seemed\Nto use it lately, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those photographs?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.12,0:18:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband's students.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, even those who set\Nout on their own or gave up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.72,0:18:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, miss. Who's that guy\Nwith the black hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.30,0:18:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's Kinoshita-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.97,0:18:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a genius among geniuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.93,0:18:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, he died in\Nhis youth fourteen years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in a training accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.94,0:18:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's the only\Nphoto without dust on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.02,0:18:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered if someone\Nhad been taking care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:19:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right. Was it my husband?\NHe was especially fond of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.66,0:19:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so this is where he\Nswallowed the poison and collapsed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.58,0:19:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The room is still exactly as it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.33,0:19:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those cards were in the pile of\Ncards on this desk. As was the glue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.01,0:19:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an unusually thick wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.35,0:19:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He enjoyed classical music,\Nand always listened to it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.89,0:19:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had the room soundproofed\Nso he could play the music loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, nobody would be able to\Nhear shouts coming from this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.61,0:19:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the door can be easily\Nunlocked from the inside
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.66,0:19:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even when locked from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've gone outside to get\Nhelp if he realized he was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.79,0:19:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the fact that he stayed in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.29,0:19:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam. Suicide is the\Nonly possibility I can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.84,0:19:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, look at the body mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.43,0:20:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His hands are by his side,\Nin a well-mannered way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.68,0:20:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In tv and stuff, when\Nsomeone is poisoned,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.35,0:20:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't they put their hands to\Ntheir throat or chest like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\Na policeman did say
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.69,0:20:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the body seemed a bit odd\Nfor someone who was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.78,0:20:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you found his body,\Nyou're sure he hadn't been strangled?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When all four of us found him,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.12,0:20:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we panicked and\Nhurried to call an ambulance,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.87,0:20:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they said no one\Nhad used rope on him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, couldn't he have\Nbeen strangled with a thin thread?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.84,0:20:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, like what\Nthey use in magic tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense. Even if you couldn't\Nsee it itself, it'd still leave a mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there was such a mark,\Nthe cops would've found it long ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.10,0:20:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. When he died,\Nwas he wearing these rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:21:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. His best trick involved\Nusing invisible strings on his rings
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make things seem alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.82,0:21:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had probably been\Npracticing it that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he only had the rings on.\NThere weren't any strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then that's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relief?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.58,0:21:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, if the strings\Ngot tangled up behind him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.71,0:21:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't be able to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? It's hard to get up if\Nyou can't use your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.55,0:21:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And using the\Ndoorknob would be hard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.47,0:21:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.14,0:21:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband had rings on both\Nhands tied with string or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.93,0:21:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His thumbs, most likely!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence of this would\Nremain on the body, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.40,0:21:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, by cutting that string\Nbefore the police arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.57,0:21:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would look like he had\Nordinary ring marks on his fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.11,0:21:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband was poisoned\Nbefore you and the pupils left!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.95,0:21:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The string was cut by\Nsomeone when the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.33,0:21:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,probably during all the commotion!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.87,0:21:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you're saying my husband was--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.25,0:22:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!\NYour husband was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By one of the three\Nwho found his body with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.01,0:22:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do those cards mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.35,0:22:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the Ace and Jack\Nthat were lying over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.93,0:22:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! I'm trying to figure that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.56,0:22:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, there was a phone in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.31,0:22:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even without thumbs, it shouldn't\Nbe too hard to press the buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.28,0:22:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.61,0:22:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, speaking of the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.32,0:22:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...when we found the body,\NI rushed upstairs to call an ambulance
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.45,0:22:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I didn't notice it right away,\Nbut this phone was buried in cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.00,0:22:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buried?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.46,0:22:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! The killer hid the phone!\NTo keep the victim from using it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.84,0:22:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, wouldn't it still be easy\Nto find if you tried hard enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.22,0:22:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.80,0:22:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the phone in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.10,0:23:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.\NLet me see those cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.23,0:23:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See this symbol here?\NIt's the same shape as the cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.15,0:23:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The redial button...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.94,0:23:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! These cards are a dying\Nmessage from your husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,telling us to press the redial button!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.87,0:23:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my guess is right, it should connect
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.21,0:23:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to someone your husband\Nleft a message with.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.34,0:23:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This number is not in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.51,0:23:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.22,0:23:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police found that number too,\Nbut it was nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.97,0:23:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we assumed it was\Nmy daughter playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.97,0:23:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.43,0:23:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are these numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.81,0:23:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid. What are you writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"One two six eight seven\None three two four eight nine..."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.57,0:23:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.95,0:23:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose way?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.83,0:24:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!\NCould these numbers mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.63,0:24:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I get it!\NThat's how this code works!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, this code means...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.06,0:24:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! It's out of lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.65,0:24:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, do you have a pen or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.44,0:24:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fountain pen\Nin the desk, if that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.98,0:24:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's strange.\NMy husband always had it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even his trick color pens are gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.53,0:24:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long're you\Ngonna look at those numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.28,0:24:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police are right.\NIt was the daughter playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took our daughter\Nto the show that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.16,0:24:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they assumed she entered\Nthose numbers before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.21,0:24:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning your husband didn't use\Nthe phone that day for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.34,0:24:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.34,0:24:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, the killer poisoned the\Nvictim before everyone left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.18,0:25:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Probably using a capsule\Nthat dissolved during the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.69,0:25:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the victim was stuck\Nin here the entire time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.02,0:25:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I think I'd try to\Nleave a clue about who did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.94,0:25:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I guess he couldn't!\NThere were no pens in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.91,0:25:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All there was was this phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.91,0:25:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dumb. If the victim used the\Nphone, he would've called for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.92,0:25:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, huh? I doubt the\Nphone was unplugged or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.92,0:25:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Unplugged?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.71,0:25:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.84,0:25:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer locked your husband\Nin here after unplugging the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.43,0:25:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it was plugged back in\Nduring all the commotion later on!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.52,0:25:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.93,0:25:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All three suspects are magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.81,0:25:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They could all pull\Noff such a stealthy trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.65,0:25:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer also hid\Nthe phone with the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.32,0:25:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.61,0:26:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be clear the phone was\Nunplugged if someone tried to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.32,0:26:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your husband,\Npoisoned and locked inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.95,0:26:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wanted to leave a clue\Nabout the person responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.17,0:26:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the pens were gone,\Nand the phone unplugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.46,0:26:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only option left was to use\Nthe redial button to leave a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.05,0:26:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when unplugged, as long\Nas there's power, numbers are saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.76,0:26:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, as a hint pointing to this,\Nhe left the two cards on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.48,0:26:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then my husband really\Ndid enter those numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.07,0:26:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He re-hid the phone under the cards
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.03,0:26:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because if someone used the phone\Nlater, his number would be erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.20,0:26:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, if the phone stood out too much,\Nthe killer might get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.62,0:26:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is to decipher\Nthis strange number message, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.08,0:26:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's why I--
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.50,0:26:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.30,0:26:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my pen! You wanted\Nsomething to write with, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.59,0:26:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.88,0:27:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You realized\Nsomething interesting again!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.55,0:27:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think you could tell us about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.64,0:27:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's nothing much, but look\Nat this first group of numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.48,0:27:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1-2-6-8-7-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.11,0:27:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On its own, it doesn't make much sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.32,0:27:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you connect 1, 2, 6,\N8, 7, and 1 on the phone pad,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.41,0:27:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you get a real strange shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.29,0:27:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.00,0:27:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the letter D!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.25,0:27:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So that's called a "D"?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.59,0:27:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! Then the\Nnext one, 3-2-4-8-9 is C!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.38,0:27:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! These number\Nsequences write out four characters!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.22,0:27:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adding in the 1-3-5-4-8\Nand 1-3-9-7 should leave us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.19,0:27:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the message your\Nhusband left before he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.11,0:28:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,DCMAKO?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.24,0:28:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAKO? Could that mean Mako-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.62,0:28:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.41,0:28:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she killed my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.91,0:28:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. This isn't enough to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.83,0:28:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be a message\Nhe left for Mako-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.84,0:28:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we don't know what the\N"DC" before "MAKO" means...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.30,0:28:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really amazing to figure\Nthat out from some weird numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.51,0:28:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.55,0:28:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You're really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.68,0:28:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something, Dad!\NYou're so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.27,0:28:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, this was a cinch for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.27,0:28:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.69,0:28:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is this "DC"?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.65,0:28:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only DCs I know are\NDC Brand and Washington DC...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.33,0:28:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct current...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.41,0:28:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Da capo!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.54,0:28:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the D.C.\Nthat's often in sheet music!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.25,0:28:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's read "da capo"!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.29,0:29:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\Nhe did play the piano on occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.51,0:29:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I think he often read sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.22,0:29:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what does "da capo" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.30,0:29:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means to go back\Nto the start and repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.14,0:29:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Repeat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.64,0:29:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't Mako-{\i1}san {\i0}leave\Nwith your daughter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.77,0:29:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to buy clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.77,0:29:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you contact her right away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.73,0:29:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I can. She has a pager.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.74,0:29:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's from your mom.\NShe must want us to hurry home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.54,0:29:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? But I still want to stay with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.63,0:29:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we're going\Nsomewhere really fun next, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.25,0:29:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.92,0:29:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To an even more wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.51,0:29:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Mako-{\i1}san {\i0}plans to--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.51,0:29:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She probably plans\Nto kill your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.60,0:29:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "DC Mako" your husband left behind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.19,0:30:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,likely means that Mako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}intends to repeat her murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.11,0:30:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.19,0:30:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just call the other two pupils for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.53,0:30:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll all split up and search for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.75,0:30:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano! Mako-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NWhere are you? Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.75,0:30:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.50,0:30:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.25,0:30:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.26,0:30:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No use...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.26,0:30:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Can't find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.64,0:30:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any luck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.43,0:30:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Can't find them anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.35,0:30:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we should ask\Nthe police to search now...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.35,0:30:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why would Mako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}kill my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.85,0:30:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have some\Nconnection with that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.27,0:30:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the man with the\Nblack hat in that one photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.66,0:30:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Kinoshita Yoshiro after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.16,0:30:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kinoshita? The genius magician\Nwho died fourteen years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.75,0:30:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by\N"after all," Sanada-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.41,0:31:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her when I went to\Nthe basement room one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.96,0:31:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mako was embracing a picture with care.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.55,0:31:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought something was up,\Nbut I never imagined she'd kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.22,0:31:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.85,0:31:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I was flustered\Nwhen we found the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.56,0:31:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never saw Mako cut the string\Non his rings or plug the phone back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.81,0:31:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.86,0:31:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been found out?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.53,0:31:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mako-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.86,0:31:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.66,0:31:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.41,0:31:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. She's just asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.85,0:31:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was actually going to put her\Nto sleep for a very long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.25,0:31:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just like my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.38,0:31:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.42,0:31:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The Kinoshita Yoshiro\Nyou were just talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.67,0:31:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was my brother, fourteen\Nyears older than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.55,0:31:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At only 20, he had received every\Naccolade a magician could obtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.31,0:32:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he was my only family,\Nafter our parents died when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.02,0:32:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then that man destroyed\Nmy brother like a bug!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.94,0:32:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo Motoyasu\Nwas jealous of his talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.28,0:32:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!\NMy husband would never--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.03,0:32:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a lie. I saw it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.29,0:32:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On that day, fourteen years ago,\Nhe fiddled with the handcuffs
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.00,0:32:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that my brother used in shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.67,0:32:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately after, my brother\Ndrowned in the practice water tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.92,0:32:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because his handcuffs\Nwouldn't come off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.84,0:32:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident was swept under\Nthe rug as an accident, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.43,0:32:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you became his\Npupil to avenge your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.44,0:32:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My last name was changed\Nwhen I was taken in by relatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.65,0:32:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he probably never realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.82,0:32:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother was killed\Nright on my 7th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.16,0:33:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The birthday when I was left all alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.79,0:33:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I killed him\Njust before his daughter turned 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.00,0:33:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I revealed my identity to him\Nafter I administered the poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.13,0:33:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he still seemed calm,\Nso I threatened to kill his daughter, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.30,0:33:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly lost his calm and...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.31,0:33:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! That was the\Nonly way to protect my status!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.19,0:33:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can have my life.\NJust keep my daughter out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.19,0:33:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I said, I planned to kill his\Ndaughter, but then I decided not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.07,0:33:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She did nothing wrong, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.74,0:33:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, he was a foolish man.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.24,0:33:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He naively let me tie his rings\Ntogether to show me a new trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.67,0:33:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he unwittingly\Nswallowed my poison capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.67,0:33:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Japan's greatest\Nmagician, that's a real laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.47,0:33:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true, Mako.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.59,0:34:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He knew you were going to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.81,0:34:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.52,0:34:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you. I saw you hugging\Nthe photo of your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.48,0:34:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our teacher had been with me then.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.44,0:34:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he said, "Don't tell\Nthis to anyone until the time comes."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.07,0:34:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you won, Mako.\NYour trick completely fooled the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.50,0:34:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the dying message he left\Nwon't stand as evidence at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.50,0:34:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ridicule me. I have no\Nintention of taking the stage now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.26,0:34:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go to the police\Nand lower my own curtain on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.01,0:34:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it wasn't right for me to make\NAyano-{\i1}chan {\i0}share my lot in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.32,0:34:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterward, we took Mako-{\i1}san {\i0}to the police
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.57,0:35:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and were supposed to return to\Nthe detective agency for a late dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.95,0:35:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, it's already after 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.95,0:35:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.25,0:35:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! I forgot to\Nbuy ingredients for dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.30,0:35:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay! Conan-{\i1}kun {\i0}and I'll get\Nsomething at the convenience store!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.80,0:35:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take too long. I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.56,0:35:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Say, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}. This isn't\Nthe way to the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.98,0:35:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're lost, we should go\Nback to the detective agency first.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.69,0:35:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We have to go back...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.15,0:35:45.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.86,0:35:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to your house!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.20,0:35:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?\NThis is Shinichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}'s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.37,0:35:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.87,0:35:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So, that's how\Nyou've tricked us all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.88,0:36:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.51,0:36:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.07,0:36:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Shinichi, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.70,0:36:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying?\NOf course I'm not Shinichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.00,0:36:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.08,0:36:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That reasoning, ability to take action,\Nand lack of musical knowledge!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.17,0:36:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.88,0:36:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, look closely! I'm a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.88,0:36:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably took a weird drug\NDr. Agasa made or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.47,0:36:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's really adding up!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.89,0:36:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playing dumb already!\NI have so, so much to say to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.61,0:37:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.73,0:37:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.07,0:37:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say crazy things\Nif you don't have proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.45,0:37:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's proof right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.04,0:37:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There! I've never seen\Nsuch a close look-alike before!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.21,0:37:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.75,0:37:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to fess up, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.96,0:37:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.13,0:37:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you in front of\Nour home so late at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.10,0:37:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Shinichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s mother...\NWhen did you return from L.A.?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.31,0:37:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just now. I took the last flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.23,0:37:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some things came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.77,0:37:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! If Mom blurts\Nout too much now...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.78,0:37:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.12,0:37:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing.\NLet's have your birth mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.54,0:37:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...tell us who you really are!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.21,0:38:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.67,0:38:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you, Conan-{\i1}chan{\i0}!\NIt's good to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.48,0:38:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.34,0:38:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.05,0:38:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my grandfather's brother's\Ndaughter's cousin's uncle's grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.64,0:38:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he says he's\Na relative of Dr. Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.14,0:38:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! He and I are\Nvery distant relatives!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.23,0:38:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't he look too much\Nlike Shinichi when he was little?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.11,0:38:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think? Conan-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}seems much nicer to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.57,0:38:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom's name is\NFumiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.16,0:38:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.91,0:38:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.75,0:38:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too odd for a grade-schooler\Nto be so good at figuring things out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.38,0:38:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He must've picked up\Nsome of Shinichi's qualities!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.97,0:38:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to visit all the time, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.09,0:38:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to hang out with Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.55,0:38:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love Shinichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.10,0:38:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.60,0:39:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}. Think about it.\NWould Shinichi do something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.73,0:39:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're scary, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.61,0:39:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're scary, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.83,0:39:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! I guess\NI had the wrong idea, again!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.17,0:39:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget everything I just said!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.34,0:39:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you a yummy\NSalisbury steak as an apology!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.55,0:39:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.13,0:39:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.72,0:39:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I take him for two or three days?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.84,0:39:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My vacation starts tomorrow,\Nand we haven't talked in so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.48,0:39:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that should be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.10,0:39:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you later, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.90,0:39:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.90,0:39:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.74,0:39:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.37,0:39:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, why are you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.20,0:40:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me your fight with\NDad this afternoon is the reason why.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.08,0:40:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's some way to talk\Nto the person who saved your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saved my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.05,0:40:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Dr. Agasa
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.71,0:40:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you took baths with Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.47,0:40:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't covered for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.01,0:40:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who knows what her\Nkarate would've done to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.98,0:40:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.94,0:40:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, I hope you told\NDad you were coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.90,0:40:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.57,0:40:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.99,0:40:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! I'm going\Nto live with you for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.12,0:40:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! Don't get me involved, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.74,0:40:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But whenever I'm with mini-you,\NI feel young again, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.71,0:40:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's have\Ndin-din with Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.55,0:40:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.83,0:41:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.08,0:41:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are you awake, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.84,0:41:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.25,0:41:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also came back to Japan to\Ntake care of something out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.09,0:41:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.01,0:41:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.43,0:41:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.85,0:41:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.85,0:41:48.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yabuuchi Hiromi (37) Yukiko's old classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.85,0:41:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you must be busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.02,0:41:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rush here from\Nthe other side of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.90,0:41:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to help my childhood friend, Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.24,0:41:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Where are Yusaku-{\i1}san\N{\i0}and Shinichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.78,0:42:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, those two are busy.\NBut don't worry! I brought him instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.37,0:42:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Don't tell me he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.12,0:42:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! My second son, Conan!\NI had him in Los Angeles!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.42,0:42:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.42,0:42:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a kid, but he's quite sharp!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.17,0:42:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You and your husband\Nmust be getting along well!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.93,0:42:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.43,0:42:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is it you\Nwant us to look into?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.43,0:42:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is--
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.43,0:42:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Guests, Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.35,0:42:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Yoshifusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.69,0:42:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yukiko-{\i1}san{\i0}! She used to\Nvisit all the time when she was little!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.65,0:42:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.70,0:42:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, I don't remember her.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.11,0:42:43.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yabuuchi Yoshifusa (64) Hiromi's uncle
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.78,0:42:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I did live in Brazil for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.79,0:42:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourselves at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.33,0:42:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go, Carlos!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.70,0:42:54.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Carlos (26) Yabuuchi Yoshifusa's friend
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.51,0:42:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Carlos?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.26,0:43:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Yoshifusa says he's a\Nfriend he brought back from Brazil...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.59,0:43:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.26,0:43:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me. How does\NUncle Yoshifusa seem to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.93,0:43:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.73,0:43:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like his face, voice, and feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.73,0:43:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. We used to play with him a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.48,0:43:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he went to Brazil\Nbefore I entered grade school, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.24,0:43:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it Uncle Yoshifusa\Nwho you wanted us to investigate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.95,0:43:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He returned\Nfrom Brazil three days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.79,0:43:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he seems different from before...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.87,0:43:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not show him to your dad?\NHe's your dad's little brother, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.21,0:43:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.72,0:43:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father, Yoshichika,\Ndied last month of cancer...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.55,0:43:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Cancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.35,0:43:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My mother passed\Naway fifteen years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.60,0:43:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all of Uncle Yoshifusa's\Nfriends died early on...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.44,0:43:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we're the only two who've\Nmet him on numerous occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.94,0:44:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why are you\Nso suspicious of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.07,0:44:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.57,0:44:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.95,0:44:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone suspects
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.95,0:44:13.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi's husband (married into family)
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.04,0:44:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that old man might be an impostor
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.29,0:44:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to take her father's inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.42,0:44:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He owned all the land in this area,\Nand his inheritance is worth a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.84,0:44:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lawyer says he left a will,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.55,0:44:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that anyone who's absent when\Nit's read doesn't get a single yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.60,0:44:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When is it going to be read?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.06,0:44:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow night at 10:00,\Nwhen his mourning ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.98,0:44:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means we gotta unmask
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.98,0:44:43.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yabuuchi Yoshiyuki (32) Hiromi's brother
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.53,0:44:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that old man before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:46.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yabuuchi Keiko (28) Yoshiyuki's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or else we'll end up with a smaller share.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.99,0:44:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt might not just mean a smaller share.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.99,0:44:54.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yabuuchi Machiko (39) Yoshichika's 2nd wife
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.87,0:44:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on the contents of\Nthe will, we may get nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.67,0:44:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, we gotta do something\Nbefore tomorrow night.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.92,0:45:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did all these people come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.43,0:45:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.55,0:45:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't there any old photos left?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.56,0:45:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Uncle Yoshifusa took\Nthem all when he went to Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.40,0:45:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, could this be him?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.86,0:45:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? You guys are in it too, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.57,0:45:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.36,0:45:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's him!\NThe one in the middle!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.87,0:45:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely Uncle Yoshifusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.29,0:45:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he's too young\Nin it to be of any use.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.83,0:45:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he has a hat on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.67,0:45:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this brings back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.50,0:45:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is from the city\Nbaseball tournament!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.05,0:45:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember?\NA runner's shoe spike injured his leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.76,0:45:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. He had to get\Nlots of stitches at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.35,0:45:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, shouldn't\Nhe still have that scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.31,0:45:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.69,0:46:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.90,0:46:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.24,0:46:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle! Would you like some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.74,0:46:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.74,0:46:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.53,0:46:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I'll clean it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.41,0:46:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not there!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.41,0:46:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The scar isn't there!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.21,0:46:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.08,0:46:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.83,0:46:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, do you mean this?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.34,0:46:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A runner spiked my\Nleg hard on first base
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.05,0:46:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,during a baseball game thirty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.85,0:46:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He does have a scar...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.23,0:46:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning it's really him?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.90,0:46:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you did suspect me!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.52,0:46:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother was right!\NThere are no decent people here!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.32,0:46:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wise to bring Carlos with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.86,0:46:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.86,0:46:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a bodyguard I hired in Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.62,0:46:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bodyguard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.41,0:46:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you need one?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.46,0:47:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd hire one too,\Nif you got a letter like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.29,0:47:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's no inheritance for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.09,0:47:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you value your life,\Ndon't come back."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.38,0:47:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Life?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.58,0:47:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get this letter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.83,0:47:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One month ago. It was\Nsent to my house in Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.88,0:47:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes without saying that\Nthe sender's name was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.38,0:47:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't care about my brother's\Ninheritance, but I did want to see
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.51,0:48:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the faces of the buffoons\Nwho would send such a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.56,0:48:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buffoons?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.44,0:48:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you're finished here,\Nthen get the hell out!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.86,0:48:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister!\NTeach me some kanji letters!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.32,0:48:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom won't help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.20,0:48:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Shin--
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.70,0:48:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, Conan-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.70,0:48:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you write "happy new year"?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.79,0:48:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Left-handed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.38,0:48:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see that, Sis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.67,0:48:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But I can't remember\Nif our uncle was left-handed or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.09,0:48:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.84,0:48:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.51,0:48:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he did have the scar on his leg,\Nso I think he is Uncle Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.52,0:48:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he could've heard from someone
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.98,0:48:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and relied on an old scar of\Nhis own he just happened to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.11,0:48:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that geezer is a fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.40,0:48:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he's the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.28,0:49:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at the photo of\NUncle Yoshifusa we found in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.29,0:49:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? He has a mitt on his right hand.\NProof that he's left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.83,0:49:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, his handwriting is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.21,0:49:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Handwriting?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.92,0:49:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found this postcard with the photograph!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.92,0:49:22.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy New Year
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.51,0:49:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A New Year's card that Uncle\NYoshifusa sent when he was in Brazil!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.35,0:49:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? The handwriting matches\Nexactly with what he wrote just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.10,0:49:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Don't tell me you had\Nhim write this so you could check?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.02,0:49:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what I'd expect\Nfrom the son of Kudo Yusaku,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.78,0:49:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the world-renowned mystery writer!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.45,0:49:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my son! Mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.87,0:49:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.29,0:49:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.37,0:49:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old well is still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.92,0:49:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after that accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.88,0:49:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.88,0:49:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.42,0:49:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mother fell into it and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.30,0:50:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She disappeared one day fifteen\Nyears ago, after a very heavy snowfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.76,0:50:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all looked for her,\Nbut couldn't find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.18,0:50:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next morning, just when\Nwe were about to contact the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.19,0:50:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we found her in the well, dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.90,0:50:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were going to destroy\Nthe well because it was dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.61,0:50:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Father asked to keep it until he\Ndied too, so he'd never forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.74,0:50:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why there's\Na fence around the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.20,0:50:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went and put it there myself,\Nso nobody else'd fall in.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.21,0:50:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the real trouble was\Nduring the funeral before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.42,0:50:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.46,0:50:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mom's brother\Nsuddenly caused a scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.05,0:50:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claimed one of us\Nknocked her down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.97,0:50:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What really did happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.64,0:50:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause was that\Ncamellia plant our uncle grew
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.65,0:50:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a wedding gift for our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.15,0:50:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Camellia?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.69,0:50:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sasanqua next to the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.28,0:51:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mother stood on the edge of\Nthe well to pick a flower, but slipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.91,0:51:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to show it to us.\NShe loved those flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.41,0:51:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They hardly bloomed\Nduring the winter of that year,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.38,0:51:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she had been\Nwaiting for them eagerly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.51,0:51:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A camellia flower\Nwas found in her hand, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.64,0:51:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, in the end, her brother\Ndidn't seem to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.43,0:51:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Where is he now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.35,0:51:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.48,0:51:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was rather old back then,\Nso perhaps he's passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.49,0:51:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! If he's still alive,\Nwon't he get the inheritance, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.99,0:51:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! Legally, he shouldn't\Nhave any inheritance rights to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.04,0:51:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not necessarily true.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.45,0:51:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could still receive some inheritance,\Nif it's in my husband's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.71,0:51:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what, he might show\Nup before 10:00 tomorrow night,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.92,0:52:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the will is read?!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.88,0:52:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.30,0:52:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. If he's alive,\Nhe'll be absolutely sure to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.43,0:52:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he seems to have a\N15-year old grudge with you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.15,0:52:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, it has nothing\Nto do with me, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.57,0:52:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as I wasn't a part\Nof this family when she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.57,0:52:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! I'm off to a friend's\Nafter-wedding party now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.28,0:52:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave the rest to you,\NHiromi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.00,0:52:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.83,0:52:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.17,0:52:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.38,0:52:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was just there!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.01,0:52:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange person watching\Nus from behind that wood gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.43,0:52:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.02,0:52:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you weren't\Njust seeing things, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.02,0:52:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. I'm pretty\Nsure someone was here...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.19,0:53:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like this. Don't tell me\Nthis person is actually her brother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.62,0:53:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to bother you by staying here\Nand having you make such a nice meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.12,0:53:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no problem! {\i1}Nabe {\i0}dishes\Nare more fun with lots of people!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.54,0:53:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. You even\Npacked a change of clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.25,0:53:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you were planning\Nto stay from the start...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.92,0:53:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that? Did you\Nsay something, Conan-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.51,0:53:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.02,0:53:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could that be at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.69,0:53:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.52,0:53:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.85,0:53:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mother! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.02,0:53:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, we were\Nout of firewood for the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.19,0:53:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. So I thought we'd go\Nwithout using the bath tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.82,0:53:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.12,0:53:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko-{\i1}chan{\i0}! Let's drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.37,0:53:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit it! I'm on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.87,0:53:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.21,0:54:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought firewood for the bath\Nthis morning and put it by the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.55,0:54:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.17,0:54:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.09,0:54:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother seems to be quite drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.93,0:54:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She sure is carefree in\Nthe middle of Dad's mourning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.68,0:54:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! A {\i1}nabe {\i0}for dinner tonight!\NNow I can rest easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.69,0:54:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rest easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.98,0:54:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't have to ask Carlos\Nto taste-test my food for poison!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.78,0:54:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.40,0:54:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that letter\Nwas a prank or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.62,0:54:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.00,0:54:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's the water, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.46,0:54:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems just right!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.71,0:54:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, a caldron bath in these times?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.17,0:54:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what's wrong\Nwith that? It has elegance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.05,0:54:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}. Want to bathe\Ntogether like in the old days?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.55,0:54:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.01,0:54:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Could you tell\NUncle the bath is ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.64,0:54:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he did love baths!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.69,0:55:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always took the first bath, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.65,0:55:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he and that Carlos\Nperson will fit in this small bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.78,0:55:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.28,0:55:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle has taken a bath\Nevery day since he's come here,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.20,0:55:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Carlos always stayed in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.49,0:55:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? He would take a bath all alone,\Nleaving his bodyguard behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.87,0:55:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see. Carlos watches\Neveryone while he's in the bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.88,0:55:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. I'm counting on you, Carlos.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.18,0:55:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.85,0:55:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Did you find the firewood?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.27,0:55:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Uncle just went to take a bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.56,0:55:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.98,0:55:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still at the party. I don't think\NI'll be back until after 11:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.61,0:55:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to ask, but could\Nyou keep the bath warm until then?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.20,0:55:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.29,0:56:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a great bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.04,0:56:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think I'll go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.29,0:56:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll go after you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.34,0:56:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! How was the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.55,0:56:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a little cold, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.18,0:56:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I better rebuild the fire then.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.93,0:56:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.85,0:56:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.14,0:56:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourself at home!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.60,0:56:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly! You can take baths\Nwith Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}, but not with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.45,0:56:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Hiromi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.03,0:56:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,J-Just now! There was a weird man\Nwith sunglasses behind the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.41,0:56:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I did see that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.17,0:56:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Doesn't that pail seem strange?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.88,0:56:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.84,0:56:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! The well bucket is up!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.01,0:56:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like something's stuck to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.31,0:56:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's pull it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.77,0:57:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.27,0:57:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.03,0:57:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.21,0:57:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How did this happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.46,0:57:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me she jumped\Ninto the well to commit suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.30,0:57:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There's a stab mark in\Nher chest! This is how she died!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.97,0:57:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.72,0:57:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean someone here did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.85,0:57:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.60,0:57:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Machiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s last phone\Ncall was at around 9:00, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.56,0:57:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. From the banquet hall\Nof the hotel near the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.23,0:57:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went into the bath ten minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.57,0:57:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone leave the\Nroom while I was in the bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.24,0:58:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.70,0:58:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it couldn't\Nhave been someone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.29,0:58:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would take at least one hour by\Ncar from the hotel to this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.54,0:58:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, while I was in the bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.59,0:58:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she returned, and someone killed\Nher and threw her down the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.13,0:58:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, it's a different\Nstory if you suspect me,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.89,0:58:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even though I met her\Nfor the first time today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.22,0:58:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who did kill her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.77,0:58:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be the suspicious man\Nwith sunglasses you just saw?!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.10,0:58:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would he kill Mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.19,0:58:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something in her pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.15,0:58:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.44,0:58:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.45,0:58:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a camellia flower!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.86,0:58:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Then the person\NI just saw r-really was...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.33,0:58:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man from fifteen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.04,0:58:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.30,0:58:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is\NYabuuchi Machiko-{\i1}san{\i0}, age 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.30,0:59:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure she's the\Nsecond wife of Yoshichika-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.35,0:59:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the head of this house\Nwho died last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.18,0:59:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.77,0:59:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.44,0:59:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't found\Nthe murder weapon yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.52,0:59:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it appears she died of\Nblood loss from the stab to the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.53,0:59:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.49,0:59:22.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.49,0:59:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we say the body was found just after 10:00 pm?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.41,0:59:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.66,0:59:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed odd that the well bucket\Nwas up, so when we pulled it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.58,0:59:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we found her body in the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.42,0:59:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.13,0:59:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! I just got\Nchills when I imagined it...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.05,0:59:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, this would mean that\Nthe killer was one of you eight
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.81,0:59:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who were here when it happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.85,0:59:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.31,1:00:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was at a friend's after-wedding\Nparty at the hotel by the station,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.36,1:00:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she called from\Nthere at around 9:00!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.45,1:00:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she left by\Ncar right after calling,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.83,1:00:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she wouldn't be\Nback until after 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.33,1:00:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in the same room
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.67,1:00:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,between 10:00 and the\Ntime the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.09,1:00:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we couldn't have killed her!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.55,1:00:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! I was the only one not with them,\Nbecause I was in the bath!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.85,1:00:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! T-Then you're the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.52,1:00:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I only met the\Nlate Machiko-{\i1}san {\i0}today!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.27,1:00:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.90,1:00:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.90,1:00:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth!\NYukiko's been living abroad.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.53,1:00:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened\Nto ask her here today.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.66,1:00:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yukiko"? Oh, wait a minute!\NDon't tell me you're...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.08,1:00:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fujimine Yukiko-{\i1}san{\i0}, the actress?!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.04,1:00:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.29,1:00:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, cool!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.42,1:01:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to watch you every week on\N"Dangerous Policewoman Story!"
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.59,1:01:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You actually inspired me\Nto join the police!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.59,1:01:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.43,1:01:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes you even more suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.26,1:01:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.47,1:01:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're skilled\Nat using guns and knives.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.77,1:01:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just a TV show!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.15,1:01:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we gonna be alright with this cop?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.32,1:01:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Was it really\NMachiko-{\i1}san {\i0}who called?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.28,1:01:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was her.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.28,1:01:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She responded to the conversation,\Nand I could hear the party, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.83,1:01:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! Only you could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.83,1:01:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.25,1:01:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone\Nelse who's suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.42,1:01:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was lurking around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.84,1:01:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange person covering his face\Nwith sunglasses, a hat, and a scarf.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.64,1:01:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A s-strange person?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.81,1:01:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's the brother of our mom,\Nwho died fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.23,1:01:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She tried to pick a flower there\Nand accidentally fell into the well.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.69,1:02:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's convinced one\Nof us pushed her down there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.70,1:02:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But just like me, Machiko-{\i1}san {\i0}wasn't\Npart of the family fifteen years ago!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.87,1:02:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why would he kill her?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.79,1:02:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.46,1:02:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was dark back here.\NMaybe he mistook her for someone else?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.34,1:02:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, it's still not certain if\Nhe was the man with sunglasses...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.09,1:02:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.05,1:02:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Here's this camellia flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.56,1:02:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flower from that tree?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.10,1:02:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was in this\Nlady's breast pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.69,1:02:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you freakin' out for?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.28,1:02:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're with the homicide\Ndepartment, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.36,1:02:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Actually, this is my\Nfirst real investigation...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.37,1:02:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a cold going\Naround the department,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.83,1:02:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I was the only\None they could send...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.71,1:02:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I'm not good\Naround dead bodies...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.12,1:03:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.12,1:03:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.71,1:03:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyways, to find out the\Nprecise time the victim returned home,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.67,1:03:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll need to check with\Nthe taxi she took from the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.38,1:03:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taxi?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.47,1:03:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother took the family car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.01,1:03:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Car?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.52,1:03:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car's in the yard, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.48,1:03:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I didn't see one anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.44,1:03:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.86,1:03:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How strange. It's always parked here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.49,1:03:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Mother have put the car?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.20,1:03:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had been drinking at the party,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.03,1:03:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so perhaps she left the\Ncar there and took a taxi home?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.54,1:03:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.41,1:03:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.12,1:03:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.13,1:03:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a car in the\Nwoods right behind the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.09,1:03:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-In the woods?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.01,1:03:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's a car doing there?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.76,1:04:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is our car!\NBut why is it in the woods?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.10,1:04:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the killer planned to\Nuse it, but changed his mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.61,1:04:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother probably just ran\Nout of gas or had engine trouble!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.49,1:04:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she walked to the house,\Nwhere that man was waiting to stab her!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.33,1:04:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. The engine works\Njust fine, and the key was still in.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.17,1:04:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it still has gas, and\Ndoesn't seem to have any flat tires...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.13,1:04:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this empty cassette\Ncase seems curious.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.13,1:04:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see its contents anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.59,1:04:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only a cell phone\Nin the glove compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.64,1:04:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.98,1:04:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you'll all sleep\Ntonight while we keep watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.15,1:04:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, that man\Ncould still be out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.32,1:04:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. We all gotta sleep in\Nthe same room as some cops?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.33,1:05:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.21,1:05:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.54,1:05:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much have you figured out?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.29,1:05:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.13,1:05:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, tell me!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.63,1:05:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get accused of being the killer\Nif we leave it to that lamebrain cop!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.14,1:05:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are still too many mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.72,1:05:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's that man in the sunglasses,\Nthe car left in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.73,1:05:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the empty cassette case.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.94,1:05:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's most curious of all is the\Nbody that was tied to the well rope.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.94,1:05:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it was hidden in the well,\Nit almost asked to be found.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.78,1:05:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There are too many\Nmysteries scattered about.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.20,1:05:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.17,1:05:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that storeroom open before?.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.42,1:05:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.72,1:05:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.31,1:06:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.77,1:06:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's get back\Nto our room and sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.77,1:06:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.37,1:06:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.25,1:06:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.75,1:06:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found the murder weapon in the well!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.75,1:06:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.30,1:06:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A kitchen knife, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.80,1:06:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please see if it matches\Nwith the victim's stab wound.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.30,1:06:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.30,1:06:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that plastic thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.31,1:06:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's a woman's raincoat.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.48,1:06:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The knife was wrapped\Nin it for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.06,1:06:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A raincoat?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.40,1:06:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, forget it!\NAuthorized personnel only!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.94,1:06:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.44,1:06:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person just barged in...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.07,1:07:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I'm the attorney!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.78,1:07:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attorney?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.91,1:07:07.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Yabuuchi Family Attorney
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.91,1:07:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to read the will of the late Yoshichika-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.41,1:07:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.50,1:07:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.54,1:07:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Delay the reading of the will?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.84,1:07:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The killer still\Nhasn't been caught,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.13,1:07:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we haven't\Nfinished checking the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.22,1:07:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reading should\Nbe moved to a later date...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.39,1:07:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.89,1:07:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the right to decide that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.48,1:07:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The greedier you are,\Nthe more noise you make.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.31,1:07:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.52,1:07:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geezer! Don't be rude with me!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.86,1:07:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got that?!\NYou're just an impostor, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.24,1:07:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is pain the only way\Nto get through to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.75,1:07:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, you two!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.46,1:07:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about this? We police\Nwill also attend the reading. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.63,1:08:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's all be friends!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.47,1:08:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That was...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.55,1:08:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brazilian jujutsu.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.68,1:08:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's quite skilled, at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.52,1:08:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean Carlos\Nis even more skilled than him?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.61,1:08:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if he's so good at self-defense,\Nwhy would he hire a bodyguard?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.99,1:08:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good question. Maybe\Nhe's just being extra cautious.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.33,1:08:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reading of Yabuuchi Yoshichika's\Nlast will will now take place.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.96,1:08:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask that you listen quietly.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.06,1:08:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.97,1:08:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? What is that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.65,1:08:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the tape recorder?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.48,1:09:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshichika-{\i1}san {\i0}recorded a\Ntape that accompanies his written will.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.74,1:09:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I don't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.33,1:09:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, isn't that the record button?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.46,1:09:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to stop it!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.05,1:09:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duck!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.05,1:09:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.39,1:09:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.85,1:09:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The cabinet! An arrow\Ncame out of that cabinet!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.44,1:09:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.40,1:09:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.03,1:09:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A b-bow gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.95,1:09:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this clock...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.12,1:09:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A timing device...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.95,1:09:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it was set to\Nfire at a specified time...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.71,1:09:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who would do this?!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.84,1:10:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who set this up?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.81,1:10:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who set this up?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.77,1:10:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been that person\Nwho ran from the gate last night!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.39,1:10:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming he really is the brother\Nof our mom who died fifteen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.56,1:10:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and that he held a grudge\Nagainst our Yabuuchi family...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.41,1:10:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.45,1:10:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used the fact we would gather\Nin here for the reading of the will
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.33,1:10:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and set up the\Nbow gun and arrow there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.83,1:10:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean\Nanyone would've done, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.13,1:10:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it doesn't look that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.00,1:10:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.67,1:10:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Look at the room on the\Nother side of the wall it went through.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.47,1:10:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See all the arrow\Nholes in the floor mat?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.47,1:10:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof that the killer had\Ndone some test shots beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.81,1:11:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to hit the\Nperson sitting in that spot.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.19,1:11:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was decided from the start
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.44,1:11:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the will would be\Nread in that room, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.66,1:11:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.16,1:11:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's even more evidence, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.66,1:11:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, kid, there'd be no\Nway to tell who'd sit where.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.00,1:11:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there would.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.46,1:11:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The arrow flew at the "head seat,"
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.71,1:11:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the one furthest from the exit,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.71,1:11:31.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Seats of Honor
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.67,1:11:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where the most senior person sits, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.67,1:11:31.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Humble Seats
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.59,1:11:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, that means the\Nperson who set up the arrow...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.06,1:11:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...had tried to target you,\NUncle Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.56,1:11:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, there's still another cretin out\Nto take my life. Heaven help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.82,1:11:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, isn't this a possibility?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.36,1:11:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if Uncle was the\None who set up the arrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.45,1:12:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so. He barely dodged\Nit after reacting to Conan's voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.87,1:12:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duck!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.38,1:12:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, is all of this the doing of\Nthat strange man with the sunglasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.17,1:12:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's a very good possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.39,1:12:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... I'm sorry to interrupt...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.60,1:12:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But shouldn't we\Nstop that tape recorder?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.65,1:12:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! I left it on record!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.90,1:12:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Did all of our\Ndad's will get erased?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.95,1:12:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.24,1:12:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, whoops!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.45,1:12:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accidentally put it on\NSide B instead of Side A.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.95,1:12:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Side B was recorded to!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.58,1:12:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The will is safe and sound on Side A!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.75,1:12:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.34,1:12:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Just let us hear the will already!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.92,1:12:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down. I'm rewinding it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.30,1:12:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I don't think\Nwe'll be able to solve this case
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.18,1:12:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until we learn\Nwho that strange person is...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.18,1:13:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But I have a good\Nidea who set up the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.06,1:13:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that person.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.81,1:13:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me they're in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.78,1:13:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.82,1:13:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Who is it?! Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.20,1:13:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There are still too many mysteries!\NI can't say anything rashly!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.66,1:13:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a hint, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.12,1:13:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.33,1:13:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.21,1:13:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then! I'll figure it out\Non my own! Who needs you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.34,1:13:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! Don't pout, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.34,1:13:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.80,1:13:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a suspicious\Ncassette tape by the bath stove!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.31,1:13:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A tape?!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.22,1:13:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, everyone! Please stay\Nin this room until I return!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.77,1:13:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Huh? Where's\NYukiko-{\i1}san {\i0}and that boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.86,1:13:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They just went outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.65,1:13:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.45,1:13:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, hold on! Please\Ndon't wander around on your own!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.91,1:14:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where was this tape?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.66,1:14:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes. It was between the firewood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.46,1:14:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.71,1:14:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi got the bath ready, but she\Ndidn't say anything about a tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.38,1:14:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and we just received word\Nfrom the examiners. It's strange...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.92,1:14:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.68,1:14:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the victim's fingerprints and\Nblood were on the murder weapon,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.43,1:14:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but oddly enough, it appears\Nshe had held it as you would a sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.61,1:14:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A s-sword?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.15,1:14:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.32,1:14:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.61,1:14:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had grabbed the\Nhandle after being stabbed,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.87,1:14:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would've been upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.45,1:14:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was placed in her hands\Nto make it look like a suicide,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.62,1:14:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would've made sense\Nto have it upside down, too!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.79,1:14:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and I contacted the hotel\Nthe victim had supposedly been at.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.63,1:14:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did they say?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.38,1:15:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems she had indeed been there,\Nbut they're not sure when she left.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.72,1:15:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Hiromi\Ndid say something strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.68,1:15:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The late Machiko-{\i1}san {\i0}said\Nshe'd be home after 11:00,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.94,1:15:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so why was she back just after 10:00?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.03,1:15:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.45,1:15:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This door will take you straight\Nfrom the bath to the stove.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.91,1:15:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this stove is right next to the well,\Nwhere the body was hidden!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.42,1:15:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that tape...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.34,1:15:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.17,1:15:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear what's on the tape for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.14,1:15:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.27,1:15:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.98,1:15:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that sunglasses person\Nwas watching from this gate, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.65,1:15:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Hiromi-{\i1}san\N{\i0}saw him run from there, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.62,1:16:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.37,1:16:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.00,1:16:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Please return to the room!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.83,1:16:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's go listen to\Nthat tapey-wapey, Conan-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.26,1:16:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit talking like that!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.67,1:16:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko-{\i1}chan{\i0}! Let's drink!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.97,1:16:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is from the party Mother was at!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.35,1:16:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This tape was really\Nright next to the stove?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.14,1:16:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.27,1:16:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought! This makes all\Nof Machiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s strange actions fit!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.61,1:16:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And her killer was the one\Nwho blurted out something odd!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.24,1:16:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mom. I'm gonna need your help.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.62,1:16:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured out who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.45,1:16:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to explain using\Nyour voice, so go along with it...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.46,1:16:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.13,1:16:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.67,1:17:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me that. You wouldn't\Ntell me anything earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.46,1:17:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanna do it, do it on your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.68,1:17:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I know something\Nyou don't, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.26,1:17:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Like what?!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.18,1:17:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.14,1:17:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. Just don't get in my way.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.44,1:17:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's hear the tape with\Nthe will for now. What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.44,1:17:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.58,1:17:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Detective?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.83,1:17:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I'd like to say, but the will\Ncan wait until after my explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.75,1:17:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After I've revealed who was\Nresponsible for the two incidents here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.88,1:17:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.47,1:17:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start with the second incident,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.47,1:17:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the hidden bow gun\Nthat was aimed at Mr. Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.68,1:17:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now. Wasn't the guy\Nwith the sunglasses behind that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.06,1:17:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.27,1:17:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I heard a certain\Nsomeone say a certain something.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.61,1:18:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certain something?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.15,1:18:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we give it a listen?\NWe do have it...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.90,1:18:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...on Side B of the will tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.45,1:18:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Attorney. Please play it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.91,1:18:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.46,1:18:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let's play it and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.63,1:18:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duck!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.38,1:18:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.00,1:18:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.30,1:18:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The cabinet! An arrow\Ncame out of that cabinet!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.97,1:18:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.18,1:18:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A b-bow gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.05,1:18:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what about this?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.76,1:18:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.02,1:18:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you all know, the\Narrow fired from the cabinet
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.81,1:18:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,flew across the room in an instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.40,1:18:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shot through the wall,\Nand left our field of vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.36,1:18:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, a certain person accurately\Nidentified it as an arrow,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.28,1:18:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before we even opened the cabinet\Nand found a bow gun inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.12,1:18:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.46,1:19:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keiko! Don't tell me you--
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.38,1:19:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The answer is simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.46,1:19:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because you set\Nup that bow gun, Keiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.47,1:19:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.85,1:19:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's not enough\Nto prove Keiko did it...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.14,1:19:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! I set it up! The day\NUncle Yoshifusa came back!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.94,1:19:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Keiko...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.32,1:19:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got us in debt.\NI kept it a secret from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.11,1:19:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a huge amount,\Nwith even bigger interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.74,1:19:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought if I could get\Nmy portion of the inheritance,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.62,1:19:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could pay it all off\Nwithout you ever knowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.04,1:19:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, when I heard your uncle\Ncame back from Brazil, I just snapped.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.80,1:19:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't intend to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.13,1:19:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to scare\Nhim enough to return to Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.39,1:19:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set it up so it'd miss him;
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.72,1:19:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect it to fly so close to him!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.85,1:20:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter,\Nsince you killed Mother anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.15,1:20:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.40,1:20:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was your doing too, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.48,1:20:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! That wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.65,1:20:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.16,1:20:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! Believe me!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.91,1:20:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.29,1:20:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who murdered\NMachiko-{\i1}san {\i0}and hid her in the well...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.71,1:20:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was someone else!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.29,1:20:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.54,1:20:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.59,1:20:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.67,1:20:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Solve this right, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.30,1:20:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person responsible...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.76,1:20:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be watching!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.01,1:20:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.06,1:20:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.94,1:20:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who murdered Machiko-{\i1}san\N{\i0}and hid her body in the well...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.44,1:20:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Don't tell us it was\Nthe guy with the sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.91,1:20:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably our mom's\Nbrother, who blames us
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.87,1:21:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for her death when she fell\Ninto the well fifteen years ago!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.04,1:21:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a motive, but could you\Nsave this for until after he's caught?!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.13,1:21:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He's likely a\Ndetective someone hired
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.97,1:21:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to determine if Mr. Yoshifusa\Nreally is who he claims to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.72,1:21:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on. If he's not the killer, then...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.81,1:21:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.48,1:21:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Machiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nkiller is in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.03,1:21:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! You heard that she\Ncalled from the hotel at 9:00 last night!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.28,1:21:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she left right after calling,\Nshe'd arrive here after 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.16,1:21:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in the same room then,\Nso we couldn't have done it!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.25,1:21:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might this be possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.21,1:21:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just after 8:00, Machiko-{\i1}san\N{\i0}made her first call from the party,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.26,1:21:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then left the party immediately after.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.76,1:22:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just after 9:00, she parked\Nthe car in the woods
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.68,1:22:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and played back a tape recording\Nof the party on the car stereo
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.27,1:22:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while making her second call.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.48,1:22:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make it seem as\Nif she was still at the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.32,1:22:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was the one who was killed.\NWhy would she create an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.11,1:22:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because things wound up just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.37,1:22:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Opposite?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.12,1:22:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.04,1:22:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko-{\i1}san {\i0}planned to use\Nthat alibi trick and kill someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.00,1:22:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she wound up being\Nkilled by that person instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.47,1:22:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.38,1:22:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ironically, her trick wound up\Nhelping the alibi of her killer instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.06,1:22:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The raincoat found in the well...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.48,1:22:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She put it on beforehand to keep\Nher victim's blood off her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.45,1:22:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the camellia flower...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.78,1:23:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had it in her pocket so she could\Ndrop it at the murder scene later
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.79,1:23:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it look connected\Nto the incident fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.46,1:23:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the tape lying by the firewood,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.71,1:23:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she either dropped it on her way\Nto her target who was in the bath,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.72,1:23:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or it fell from her pocket while her\Nbody was being carried to the well.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.68,1:23:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In either case, she likely planned\Nto burn the tape in the stove.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.23,1:23:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder probably\Nhappened in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.49,1:23:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, if any blood went flying,\Nit could be cleaned away.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.78,1:23:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who is this person who\Nkilled her first in the bathroom?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.04,1:23:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s target was someone\Nfond of taking a bath every day,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.79,1:23:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the only person here whose\Nturn to use it was set in stone.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.80,1:24:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you, Yabuuchi Yoshifusa-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.60,1:24:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Uncle?! That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.39,1:24:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, Brazilian jujutsu\Nhas a certain technique...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.23,1:24:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which you twist the arm\Nof a knife-wielding attacker
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.98,1:24:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and cause the attacker to stab himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.03,1:24:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Machiko-{\i1}san {\i0}attacked,\Nyou used that move without thinking!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.70,1:24:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Increasing her share of the\Ninheritance was probably her motive.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.08,1:24:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that would be self-defense.\NWhy would he keep quiet about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.75,1:24:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he had been\Nsent two threatening letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.17,1:24:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, there's still another\Ncretin out to take my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.60,1:24:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That clearly indicates\Nsomeone had attacked him before.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.39,1:24:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, Machiko-{\i1}san\N{\i0}had also sent a threat letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.90,1:24:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Keiko-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nwho had set up the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.15,1:25:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume he tied the body to the\Nwell rope and made it easy to spot
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.44,1:25:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to serve as an example to\Nthe other intimidator.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.86,1:25:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, it was\Nself-defense, plain and simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.08,1:25:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you confess, Yoshifusa-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.58,1:25:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.42,1:25:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Who're you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.51,1:25:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with the sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.01,1:25:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.39,1:25:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tape with the will on it.\NOne listen will shed light on everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.73,1:25:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.02,1:25:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.90,1:25:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I divide my inheritance between\Nthe following six people:
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.20,1:25:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my wife Machiko, my daughter\NHiromi, her husband Hidekazu,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.28,1:25:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my son Yoshiyuki, his wife Keiko,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.54,1:25:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Carlos.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.37,1:25:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Carlos?! W-What is\Nhis name doing on here?!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.00,1:26:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby divide my inheritance\Nevenly among those six people.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.88,1:26:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange! Why isn't\Nyour name on the list, Uncle?!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.35,1:26:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.10,1:26:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, that old man is a\Nbodyguard who came here from Brazil
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.48,1:26:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep Carlos safe!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.32,1:26:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.98,1:26:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, who is Carlos?!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.65,1:26:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The son born of the real\NYoshifusa-{\i1}san {\i0}and a Brazilian woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.49,1:26:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Son?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.58,1:26:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Detective!\NWhere did you find that out?!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.08,1:26:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not a detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.92,1:26:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a mere mystery writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.55,1:26:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yusaku-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.84,1:26:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes! D-Dad!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.84,1:26:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku-{\i1}san{\i0}! \NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.47,1:26:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uhh, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.73,1:26:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But is he really not him?!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.31,1:27:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's left-handed,\Nand his handwriting matched!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.19,1:27:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is full of left-handed people.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.99,1:27:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural the handwriting matches.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.99,1:27:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Mr. Yoshifusa\Nhad the old man write for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.53,1:27:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yoshifusa and the old man\Nowned a farm in Brazil together.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.62,1:27:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when a tornado hit ten years ago,\Nthe old man hurt his right leg
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.30,1:27:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mr. Yoshifusa lost his left arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.97,1:27:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, the old man wrote for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.76,1:27:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carlos was given part of the inheritance
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.31,1:27:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because Mr. Yoshichika felt sorry\Nfor his brother who lost his farm
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.56,1:27:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had died of illness half a year prior.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.23,1:27:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all written in here,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.36,1:27:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this pile of letters left in\Na hidden panel in the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.20,1:27:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you\Npretend to be our uncle?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.62,1:27:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was to pilfer money!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.54,1:28:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that was his intent,\Nhe wouldn't have taken on the role
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.71,1:28:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of someone whose life was threatened.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.21,1:28:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If people learned\NCarlos was Mr. Yoshifusa's son,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.92,1:28:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've been\Ntargeted by the intimidators.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.84,1:28:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the old man\Ntook on the role of Mr. Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.26,1:28:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To have the intimidators'\Nattacks focused on him instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.56,1:28:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is evidenced by the fact\Nthat when the old man would bathe,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.77,1:28:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would leave Carlos\Nin the other room.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.36,1:28:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because making it seem like\Nhe was keeping watch over everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.48,1:28:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be the safest idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.57,1:28:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man planned to\Ncatch the intimidator,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.49,1:28:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but wound up killing her instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.03,1:28:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it was a case of self-defense,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.45,1:28:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've been taken\Naway by the police for questioning.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.58,1:28:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he couldn't leave Carlos alone\Nwith one other intimidator around.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.55,1:28:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made the body easy to find to\Nsee if the police detective who came
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.08,1:28:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a sensible man or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.26,1:28:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what came was\Nan unreliable rookie detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.39,1:29:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With no other choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.08,1:29:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the old man decided to remain\Nsilent until the will was read.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.60,1:29:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.40,1:29:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I get anything wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.36,1:29:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hickson Tanaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, 2nd-generation\NJapanese-Brazilian?!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.72,1:29:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly right.\NYou didn't get a single thing wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.26,1:29:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll present yourself to the police,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.87,1:29:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can introduce you to a great,\Nhardhearted inspector I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.25,1:29:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that would be best.\NI think I can trust you!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.55,1:29:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure arrived two hours later,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.63,1:29:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Tanaka-{\i1}san {\i0}and Keiko-{\i1}san {\i0}were\Ntaken to the Gunma Police Dept.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.14,1:29:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carlos, who knew very little Japanese,\Nwatched sadly as the car left,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.52,1:29:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Dad told him in Portuguese\Nthat he would be back very soon,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.57,1:29:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at which he showed child-like joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.86,1:29:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, in order to keep Carlos safe,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.24,1:30:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka-{\i1}san {\i0}hadn't told\Nhim about the inheritance
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.79,1:30:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or that this was his\Nfather's family's home.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.21,1:30:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, the long night ended.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.34,1:30:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! You heard my voice?!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.88,1:30:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Dr. Agasa gave me a microphone
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.47,1:30:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that picks up sounds from your bowtie.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.77,1:30:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It helped with my deduction.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.14,1:30:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've known the\Nold man wasn't the real deal
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.23,1:30:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I'd found those letters, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.27,1:30:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I knew he was a\Nfake before reading the letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.61,1:30:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.53,1:30:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His leg scar.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.78,1:30:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A left-handed first baseman\Nwould stretch out from the left leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.24,1:30:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that old man's\Nscar was on his right leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.41,1:30:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed strange, so I scoured\Nthe storeroom and found the letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.05,1:30:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you still lack in the\Nobservation department, Shinichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.34,1:30:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.22,1:31:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you trying to act cool,\Nafter chasing after me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.93,1:31:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm just a mere mystery writer."\NYou gotta be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.89,1:31:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to be\NAkechi Kogoro or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.56,1:31:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about lame! I can't believe you!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.02,1:31:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.99,1:31:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.61,1:31:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. You don't care how others feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.12,1:31:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We leave"? Don't insult me!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.25,1:31:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Shinichi?\NYou'll get left behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.04,1:31:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.71,1:31:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any event, these incidents\Nand this marital spat are over now.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.39,1:33:10.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.81,1:33:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.10,1:33:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Ran-{\i1}kun {\i0}my regards!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.64,1:33:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. I'd watch out\Nfor Ran-{\i1}chan {\i0}if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.43,1:33:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something bugs me\Nabout that last smile of hers...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.53,1:33:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Underestimate women\Nand you'll be in a world of hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.37,1:33:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You do understand!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.70,1:33:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.93,1:33:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't be serious... can she?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.28,1:33:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.05,1:33:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...home?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.67,1:33:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Dr. Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.13,1:33:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Heard what?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.09,1:33:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going on an overnight\Ntrip somewhere, at least tell us first!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.02,1:33:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.40,1:33:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried sick!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.23,1:33:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kept calling Shinichi's\Nhouse but no one was there!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.52,1:34:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, now!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.98,1:34:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.40,1:34:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't scare me like that...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.59,1:34:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A syringe? What's she going to do with that?
